## Project Documentation Template

For EVERY project document, ALWAYS include these sections:

### 1. Security Architecture Section
- Data flow diagram showing on-premises processing
- Encryption at rest and in transit
- Access control mechanisms
- Zero external API exposure guarantee
- Visual diagram: User → Local Model → Internal DB

### 2. Compliance Considerations Section
- HIPAA compliance status (✅ or ❌)
- BAA requirements (or lack thereof - emphasize "no BAA required")
- Data minimization techniques
- De-identification processes
- Audit trail capabilities

### 3. Scalability to Production PHI Section
- Infrastructure requirements (on-premises servers)
- Security controls for production (encryption, access logging)
- Compliance certifications (HIPAA, SOC 2, HITRUST, ISO 27001)
- Risk mitigation strategies

### 4. ROI/Business Value Quantification Section
- Specific ROI ratios (e.g., "2.8-4.1x ROI")
- Cost savings with numbers (e.g., "$380K annual value")
- Efficiency gains (e.g., "93% recall, 87% precision")
- Impact metrics (e.g., "$148M+ documented impact")
- Comparison to industry benchmarks

